    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "9c3e4bce46767370",
      "text": "Growing up as a white man in Colorado, perhaps the clearest social expectation of me has been: \"Man up!\" or more often \"Don't be a sissy!\" That kind of language is how boys trying to become men, trying to prove they are men, pick fights. The vast majority of white men in this country will have deep scars of being separated from their peers for having failed to be man enough. Moreover, we men are offered no skills for facing or healing this emotional wound. We're expected to just shut up and take it like a man."
    },
